building training such as preparation of resume  interviewing skills  oral and poster presentation skills  leadership skills and ability to work as a team all during the two months of internship training  Each student is paid a stipend sponsored by Thermo Fisher Scientific The University of Illinois College of Medicine Rockford and Thermo Fisher Scientific Summer Science Internship is an opportunity for local high school students to interact closely with professionals in either an academic or industrial research environment week program gain valuable hands on laboratory skills using a variety of scientific techniques      HS SUMMER SCIENCE APPLICATION      HS SUMMER SCIENCE APPLICATION Key dates        Mail signed and completed application along with three     signed letters of reference       Mandatory meeting to learn about the program and the specific research projects being offered       Selected students will begin their internship with orientation and training       Students will present their experience through oral presentations and scientific posters Please complete the      Summer Science Internship Program Application  sign and return by mail with required documents to  Janet Stull Snow College of Medicine Rockford Department of Biomedical Sciences      Parkview Avenue Rockford If you have questions regarding the program  please contact Janet Stull Snow at  jlss uic edu jlss uic edu About Education Research Patient Care Departments News Giving INFORMATION FOR  Prospective and Current Students Faculty   Staff Alumni   Friends Patients Businesses and Community RESOURCES  UIC Directory Blackboard Emergency Information Contact Us Apply Now Give Contact Us If you have questions  comments  or problems accessing this site  please E mail the webmaster College of Medicine Chicago Peoria Rockford Urbana 